WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.440 --> 00:00:05.610
FEMALE SPEAKER: Please join
me in welcoming Bill Belew.

00:00:05.610 --> 00:00:08.149
[APPLAUSE]

00:00:08.149 --> 00:00:09.690
BILL BELEW: I didn't
do anything yet,

00:00:09.690 --> 00:00:12.210
so I wouldn't clap
until I was finished.

00:00:12.210 --> 00:00:16.540
So I am going to do something
that, as far as I know,

00:00:16.540 --> 00:00:19.460
has never been done before.

00:00:19.460 --> 00:00:22.930
And I'm going to
do it just for you.

00:00:22.930 --> 00:00:26.060
Now the reason I say that is,
about five, six weeks ago,

00:00:26.060 --> 00:00:29.010
I came to this room-- the
tour brought me up here--

00:00:29.010 --> 00:00:32.509
I stood here, and I looked,
and I closed my eyes.

00:00:32.509 --> 00:00:36.380
And during the time I was
preparing for this talk--

00:00:36.380 --> 00:00:38.600
many times-- I
closed my eyes, and I

00:00:38.600 --> 00:00:42.510
tried to imagine who
would be sitting here.

00:00:42.510 --> 00:00:43.463
And it was you.

00:00:43.463 --> 00:00:46.460
I am not bringing
something else and hoping

00:00:46.460 --> 00:00:48.030
that you will be interested.

00:00:48.030 --> 00:00:50.540
I am bringing something
for you and hoping

00:00:50.540 --> 00:00:52.420
that other people
may be interested.

00:00:52.420 --> 00:00:55.810
And if they are
not, that's OK, too.

00:00:55.810 --> 00:00:59.070
This talk is for you.

00:00:59.070 --> 00:01:01.830
Now, the reason I
say, as far as I know,

00:01:01.830 --> 00:01:05.519
nobody's ever done this before,
is I'm almost 60 years old.

00:01:05.519 --> 00:01:07.450
Three months from now,
I'll be 60 years old.

00:01:07.450 --> 00:01:08.600
And I'm a churchgoer.

00:01:08.600 --> 00:01:11.380
So in 60 years, I've been
to church almost every week,

00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.560
probably every week,
more than once a week.

00:01:13.560 --> 00:01:18.200
So 60 times 50, that's
about 3,000, maybe 4,000.

00:01:18.200 --> 00:01:22.500
Without exaggerating, I have
heard maybe 5,000 talks.

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:24.870
I have probably
given 2,000 talks.

00:01:24.870 --> 00:01:26.980
I go to conferences
the same as you do,

00:01:26.980 --> 00:01:29.480
and I hear these
talks all of the time.

00:01:29.480 --> 00:01:32.490
And so I am pretty sure,
somewhere between 7,000

00:01:32.490 --> 00:01:35.310
and 10,000 talks I
have heard or given,

00:01:35.310 --> 00:01:39.590
and nobody has ever done
what I'm going to do today.

00:01:39.590 --> 00:01:41.530
We hope it will work, right?

00:01:41.530 --> 00:01:44.270
So the idea for what
I'm going to do today

00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:46.730
came from my children.

00:01:46.730 --> 00:01:50.030
My oldest son is a piano player.

00:01:50.030 --> 00:01:51.280
And I think he's very good.

00:01:51.280 --> 00:01:53.680
But then, all parents will
think their kids are good.

00:01:53.680 --> 00:01:57.367
Well, he writes
these piano pieces.

00:01:57.367 --> 00:01:59.075
And if you listen to
them very carefully,

00:01:59.075 --> 00:02:03.460
you will hear that there are
two songs going on out of sync.

00:02:03.460 --> 00:02:05.275
They are not matching together.

00:02:05.275 --> 00:02:09.120
So we hear two songs going--
one here, one there-- right?

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:11.074
So it's called counterpoint.

00:02:11.074 --> 00:02:12.490
So you would play
a song, and then

00:02:12.490 --> 00:02:15.390
there's another song, that,
ha, I can hear that, too.

00:02:15.390 --> 00:02:17.815
Well, and then my other
son is a scientist.

00:02:17.815 --> 00:02:22.260
And he's a biologist,
a bioscientist.

00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:27.820
So he knows how wonderfully
the body will work together.

00:02:27.820 --> 00:02:30.740
Now, my right hand doesn't know
what my left hand is doing.

00:02:30.740 --> 00:02:33.840
Sometimes, I can write
and listen and tap my foot

00:02:33.840 --> 00:02:36.080
while listening to
music at the same time.

00:02:36.080 --> 00:02:40.310
They're all not together, but
they all work together, right?

00:02:40.310 --> 00:02:43.610
And then, I have a six-year-old.

00:02:43.610 --> 00:02:45.772
And you say, what
is a 60-year-old man

00:02:45.772 --> 00:02:46.855
doing with a six-year-old?

00:02:46.855 --> 00:02:49.397
Well, that's none
of your business.

00:02:49.397 --> 00:02:50.605
But I do have a six-year-old.

00:02:53.400 --> 00:02:56.045
How many of you have
seen the movie "Frozen?"

00:02:56.045 --> 00:02:59.040
Where have you been? "Frozen,"
let it go, let it go, right?

00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:01.615
Well, Anna is singing
one song, and Elsa

00:03:01.615 --> 00:03:03.610
is singing another song.

00:03:03.610 --> 00:03:05.210
And you can hear
them going, depending

00:03:05.210 --> 00:03:08.080
on which side you
listen out of, right?

00:03:08.080 --> 00:03:10.610
So there are two things always
going on at the same time.

00:03:10.610 --> 00:03:13.630
But they match more or less.

00:03:13.630 --> 00:03:14.885
So I'm going to try.

00:03:14.885 --> 00:03:16.340
No, I'm not going to try.

00:03:16.340 --> 00:03:20.736
I'm going to give you two
talks at the same time.

00:03:20.736 --> 00:03:22.720
Hm.

00:03:22.720 --> 00:03:25.890
One of them is going
to be on the slides.

00:03:25.890 --> 00:03:28.830
Just watch the slides.

00:03:28.830 --> 00:03:31.050
The other one is going
to be what I say.

00:03:31.050 --> 00:03:33.480
They're not going
to be the same.

00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:35.050
But they will be
somewhat the same.

00:03:35.050 --> 00:03:36.591
But they're not
going to be the same.

00:03:36.591 --> 00:03:41.790
So if your thing is watching and
not listening, then just watch.

00:03:41.790 --> 00:03:49.820
There will be 15 points, that
if you do only those 15 points,

00:03:49.820 --> 00:03:51.440
you will be able to communicate.

00:03:51.440 --> 00:03:53.686
You will be able
to talk to anybody

00:03:53.686 --> 00:03:54.935
from any country in the world.

00:03:54.935 --> 00:03:57.690
Just do those 15.

00:03:57.690 --> 00:03:59.870
And they should be pretty
easy to understand just

00:03:59.870 --> 00:04:01.380
by looking at them.

00:04:01.380 --> 00:04:03.810
And if you want to be
really, really good,

00:04:03.810 --> 00:04:05.350
do more than those 15.

00:04:05.350 --> 00:04:06.710
So just pick one.

00:04:06.710 --> 00:04:07.410
Just do that.

00:04:07.410 --> 00:04:08.870
If you just do
that, oh, you will

00:04:08.870 --> 00:04:11.510
be able to talk
across any country.

00:04:11.510 --> 00:04:13.590
And if you do two of them,
you'll be really good.

00:04:13.590 --> 00:04:15.520
And if you do three of them,
you'll be really, really good.

00:04:15.520 --> 00:04:16.720
And what if you do 15?

00:04:16.720 --> 00:04:18.303
You'll be really, really,
really, really, really, really,

00:04:18.303 --> 00:04:19.827
really, really,
really, really good.

00:04:19.827 --> 00:04:20.660
I think that was 15.

00:04:20.660 --> 00:04:21.850
I'm not quite sure.

00:04:21.850 --> 00:04:23.860
So just watch the 15.

00:04:23.860 --> 00:04:24.830
Write those down.

00:04:24.830 --> 00:04:26.960
Go home, and master those.

00:04:26.960 --> 00:04:29.189
Make that what you want to do.

00:04:29.189 --> 00:04:30.730
And no matter what
culture you go to,

00:04:30.730 --> 00:04:33.110
they will understand
what you are saying.

00:04:33.110 --> 00:04:35.930
Now, if watching's not your
thing but listening is,

00:04:35.930 --> 00:04:37.830
I'm going to tell
you three stories.

00:04:37.830 --> 00:04:39.230
I will tell you three stories.

00:04:39.230 --> 00:04:42.440
Do you know, the
number one reason

00:04:42.440 --> 00:04:45.200
why people are bad speakers?

00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:48.350
There's one reason that's bigger
than all of the other reasons

00:04:48.350 --> 00:04:49.300
put together.

00:04:49.300 --> 00:04:51.720
There's one reason why
people are very bad speakers.

00:04:51.720 --> 00:04:54.840
And I know this, because
I have interviewed--

00:04:54.840 --> 00:04:57.235
I have talked to
people-- from China.

00:04:57.235 --> 00:04:58.610
I've talked to
people from Korea.

00:04:58.610 --> 00:05:00.151
I've talked to people
from Indonesia.

00:05:00.151 --> 00:05:02.040
I've talked to people
from South America.

00:05:02.040 --> 00:05:04.752
I have talked to people
from, I don't know how many,

00:05:04.752 --> 00:05:05.585
different countries.

00:05:05.585 --> 00:05:09.880
And I ask them this question,
and I get the same answer.

00:05:15.629 --> 00:05:16.420
So they come to me.

00:05:16.420 --> 00:05:17.670
I what to learn English, Bill.

00:05:17.670 --> 00:05:18.680
OK, that works for me.

00:05:18.680 --> 00:05:21.690
So if you could speak
English, and you understood

00:05:21.690 --> 00:05:25.770
and, well, could speak it
perfectly, what would you say?

00:05:28.362 --> 00:05:31.420
Yeah, you see, there's
the point there.

00:05:31.420 --> 00:05:33.330
I have asked 1,000 people.

00:05:33.330 --> 00:05:34.530
I have asked 2,000 people.

00:05:34.530 --> 00:05:38.080
If you could speak my language
perfectly, what would you say?

00:05:38.080 --> 00:05:41.510
And they say, nothing.

00:05:41.510 --> 00:05:45.250
Because they don't have
what it is they want to say.

00:05:45.250 --> 00:05:47.490
You see, if you don't
know what you want to say,

00:05:47.490 --> 00:05:49.570
you're not going to
be able to say it.

00:05:49.570 --> 00:05:52.010
If you have something
you want to say,

00:05:52.010 --> 00:05:53.680
you will find a way to say it.

00:05:53.680 --> 00:05:55.390
It always works that way.

00:05:55.390 --> 00:05:59.514
Now, I have come up with three
steps, three different steps--

00:05:59.514 --> 00:06:00.930
I will call them
levels, but we'll

00:06:00.930 --> 00:06:02.830
call them steps--
three different steps.

00:06:02.830 --> 00:06:06.980
There are things that
people want to say.

00:06:06.980 --> 00:06:10.320
There are things that
people need to say.

00:06:10.320 --> 00:06:14.110
And then there are things
that people have to say.

00:06:14.110 --> 00:06:15.840
They are different.

00:06:15.840 --> 00:06:17.620
The things that
people want to say

00:06:17.620 --> 00:06:21.440
will live on the tip, on
the end, of their tongue.

00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:23.330
The things that
people need to say

00:06:23.330 --> 00:06:26.791
will dig inside their
belly [GROWLING].

00:06:26.791 --> 00:06:28.290
And then the things
that people have

00:06:28.290 --> 00:06:33.030
to say, they will
burn in their bones.

00:06:33.030 --> 00:06:33.686
It's different.

00:06:33.686 --> 00:06:35.310
So I'm going to tell
you three stories.

00:06:35.310 --> 00:06:36.400
So we'll go through.

00:06:36.400 --> 00:06:38.710
Watch the slides, or
listen, or try to do both.

00:06:38.710 --> 00:06:40.200
You guys are smart.

00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:42.386
You should be able
to do that, right?

00:06:42.386 --> 00:06:44.110
Is anybody here besides me?

00:06:44.110 --> 00:06:45.400
Yeah, you can do that.

00:06:45.400 --> 00:06:51.540
So I was in Bangkok.

00:06:51.540 --> 00:06:52.680
And there was a room.

00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:54.750
There were probably
not more than 20 people

00:06:54.750 --> 00:06:56.030
in the room at the same time.

00:06:56.030 --> 00:07:00.730
And in those 20 people,
12 or 14 of them all

00:07:00.730 --> 00:07:02.614
came from a different country.

00:07:02.614 --> 00:07:03.780
And they were sitting there.

00:07:03.780 --> 00:07:05.870
They're talking in English,
back and forth, back and forth.

00:07:05.870 --> 00:07:07.470
They are talking to each other.

00:07:07.470 --> 00:07:11.450
And they were saying, we
have written something,

00:07:11.450 --> 00:07:14.030
but nobody will read it.

00:07:14.030 --> 00:07:16.760
We have written this paper.

00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:18.760
We have written this story.

00:07:18.760 --> 00:07:22.270
But we can't get anybody
to read the story for us.

00:07:22.270 --> 00:07:23.440
What are we going to do?

00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:26.530
So their solution, their
answer to that problem,

00:07:26.530 --> 00:07:31.015
was let's just share with
each other and pass it around.

00:07:31.015 --> 00:07:33.140
And then, hopefully, people
will pay us to do that.

00:07:33.140 --> 00:07:34.600
Well, good luck with that.

00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:36.280
Let me know how that works.

00:07:36.280 --> 00:07:39.060
And so they complained.

00:07:39.060 --> 00:07:40.620
They argued so much.

00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:41.510
I have this material.

00:07:41.510 --> 00:07:43.440
I don't know what to do with it.

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:45.520
I could not take it anymore.

00:07:45.520 --> 00:07:49.490
I said, don't you people
know about Google?

00:07:52.260 --> 00:07:54.240
So you don't know what you do.

00:07:54.240 --> 00:07:56.320
But I know how it plays
out on the other side.

00:07:56.320 --> 00:07:58.860
So I said, don't you
know about Google?

00:07:58.860 --> 00:08:00.860
Google has made it
possible-- seriously,

00:08:00.860 --> 00:08:04.410
I'm running around the world
telling about you guys.

00:08:04.410 --> 00:08:07.195
Thank you very much for what
you do-- if you write something

00:08:07.195 --> 00:08:12.430
good, you can put
that on the internet,

00:08:12.430 --> 00:08:15.000
on this magic
whatever, and people

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:16.650
will find it and read it.

00:08:16.650 --> 00:08:20.100
And they thought, wow, I cannot
give stuff away for free.

00:08:20.100 --> 00:08:20.990
Are you crazy?

00:08:20.990 --> 00:08:23.710
Why would I give
it away for free?

00:08:23.710 --> 00:08:26.930
I cannot give something
good away for free.

00:08:26.930 --> 00:08:30.170
How will I make
money doing that?

00:08:30.170 --> 00:08:32.240
I know the answer to
that question, you see.

00:08:32.240 --> 00:08:36.309
And so I now travel the
world telling people

00:08:36.309 --> 00:08:38.907
how to use what it
is you have made.

00:08:38.907 --> 00:08:39.740
Thank you very much.

00:08:39.740 --> 00:08:42.360
You have given me a job.

00:08:42.360 --> 00:08:46.355
Well, a year after that,
I went to Kuala Lumpur.

00:08:46.355 --> 00:08:47.980
And there were the
same kind of people,

00:08:47.980 --> 00:08:49.330
